 A LAWMAKER representing Obokun/Oriade Federal Constituency of Osun State, in the House of Representatives, Hon. Wole Oke has donated bags of rice worth about N15 million to the Osun state COVID-19 committee. The donation is meant to cushion the effects of the lockdown on the people of the state. The lawmaker in a statement issued in Abuja on Thursday, the lawmaker who is Chairman of the House Committee on Public Accounts, urged that the rice be distributed to everyone irrespective of party affiliation. He said: “On behalf of myself and family, we are donating N15m worth of rice to Osun State COVID-19 Relief Committee for onward distribution to the people of the state. “This is not the time to play politics, as of today, we have a common problem at hand which is ravaging the country and indeed the entire world, so, we must unite together and confront it collectively so that we can end it and have a state and a country we call our own.”